Instruction: Final diagnosis (two failures detected):

Failure 1:
- Root cause component: node-5
- Root cause occurrence datetime (UTC+8): 2022-03-20 13:30:00
- Root cause reason: node disk read I/O consumption / node I/O hotspot (high system.io.rkb_s observed; severity score 64.0; full-window 31-minute run 13:30–14:00).
- Evidence summary: metric system.io.rkb_s on node-5 shows a sustained, large read-bytes/sec spike from 13:30 that exceeds global thresholds by a large margin; multiple node I/O and load KPIs (r_s, r_await, load) also show concurrent abnormalities. error_logs contain no entries for corroboration; this is a node-level resource issue.

Failure 2:
- Root cause component: shippingservice-0 (container)
- Root cause occurrence datetime (UTC+8): 2022-03-20 13:30:00
- Root cause reason: container memory failure / high container memory pressure (container_memory_failures metrics on shippingservice-0, severity ~33.0, sustained for 13:30–14:00)
- Evidence summary: container.node-6.container_memory_failures.* KPIs for shippingservice-0 are high and sustained throughout the window. Traces to/from shippingservice show low latency and near-zero error_rate and logs show log.error_count = 0, indicating request-level traces/logs did not capture obvious errors, but the container-level memory failure metric indicates a resource-level fault at the container. The container metrics reference node-6, indicating the problematic shippingservice container runs on node-6 (container metrics include the node mapping).

Notes and confidence:
- Both faults start at the earliest anomalous timestamp 2022-03-20 13:30:00 (UTC+8) and persist through the investigated window.
- Confidence is high that node-5 I/O is a true node-level failure (large severity, multiple I/O/load KPIs). Confidence is high that shippingservice-0 experienced a container memory-related failure (sustained memory-failure KPI). Traces/logs did not show request-level errors for shippingservice, so impact may be resource-level rather than application error logs.
- Recommended next actions: inspect node-5 disk I/O and affected pods on node-5 for I/O saturation; inspect shippingservice-0 container memory events on node-6 (OOM kills, container restart events, memory limits) and host/container logs around 2022-03-20 13:30:00 to confirm cause and remediation steps.
